OL,4,CGreensill: Top civil servant 'joined
OL,5,Cfirm before quitting'
OL,6, A leading civil servant joined
OL,7, financial firm Greensill Capital as an
OL,8, adviser while still working for the
OL,9, government, a lobbying watchdog says.
OL,11,FBill Crothers's part-time position had
OL,12,Fbeen "agreed" to by the Cabinet Office,
OL,13,Fthe Office of the Advisory Committee on
OL,14,FBusiness Appointments adds.
OL,16,FIts chairman Lord Eric Pickles
OL,17,Fcomplained of a "lack of transparency"
OL,18,Fover the situation.
OL,20,FMr Crothers said he had been taken on
OL,21,Fby Greensill in a "transparent" manner.
